2025-06-11 11:03:38.731 | DEBUG    | models.series:read:224 - data: {
  "series_title": "Dissonance",
  "description": "In a gripping tale of duality and self-discovery, Eli navigates the contrasting realms of a strikingly utopian future and our flawed present-day Earth. Initially skeptical of the seemingly perfect society around him, Eli perceives the future as a delusion, leading him to behave in ways that baffle the utopian inhabitants. To them, Eli represents an enigma—his actions are viewed as paradoxical, self-defeating, and discordant with their ideals of a flawless existence.\n\nAs Eli unwittingly introduces subtle yet significant imperfections into this meticulously crafted utopia, he triggers a series of unexpected problems. While the utopians see these anomalies as harbingers of impending disaster, Eli remains blissfully unaware, interpreting them as just part of the fabric of life.\n\nWhen he's thrust back into the 'real world,' Eli finds himself yearning for the utopian ideals he once dismissed. This longing ignites a quest to impose changes upon the perfection he has witnessed, believing that even a hint of the utopia can elevate life on Earth. However, he soon confronts the stark truth that while the utopia appears metastable, thriving in its own flawed perfection, the real world is built on resilience and stability—an intricate balance that he struggles to understand.\n\nAs Eli attempts to reconcile these two existences, he discovers that true perfection may lie not in an idealized future, but in embracing the complexities of imperfection.",
  "publisher": "neon-abyss"
}
